Hi Mikkel,

I have just installed Madrake Linux 10.0 primarily to check out the Mono 
project. Since it comes with gcc 3.3.2 I thought I&#39;d try compiling NEAT 
myself, I downloaded Vinod&#39;s code but I get the following error right 
before compiling even starts:

---------------------------
g++ -o3 -g -Wall -Wno-return-type -I/usr/include/g++-2 
-I/usr/lib/gtkmm/include -I/usr/lib/glib/include -I/usr/include/gtk-1.2 
-I/usr/include/glib-1.2 -I/usr/include/sigc++-1.0 
-I/usr/lib/sigc++-1.0/include -DSWIG_GLOBAL -c networks.cpp -o networks.o
cc1plus: error: unrecognized option `-strip&#39;
cc1plus: error: output filename specified twice
make: *** [networks.o] Error 1
---------------------------

I checked it out and it&#39;s a bug in gcc related to the -o option (see 
http://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=13577). There is a patch but 
I don&#39;t really want to get drawn into patching recompiling gcc right now!

Colin.




